    "body" : "<p>I'm looking for a function that checks only if it's one of the Latin letters or a decimal number. Since <code>char c = 255</code>, which in printable version is <strong>├</strong> and considered as a letter by <code>Character.isLetter(c)</code>.\nThis function I think is what most developers are looking for:</p>\n\n<pre><code>private static boolean isLetterOrDigit(char c) {\n    return (c &gt;= 'a' &amp;&amp; c &lt;= 'z') ||\n           (c &gt;= 'A' &amp;&amp; c &lt;= 'Z') ||\n           (c &gt;= '0' &amp;&amp; c &lt;= '9');\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
